    "# 융 Module 9: System Integration\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the most important module yet. You will combine the two separate systems you have mastered—CAN bus telemetry and AI vision—into a single, intelligent application. This is **Sensor Fusion**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 1: Your Mission\n",
    "\n",
    "Your goal is to build a **Smart Safety Monitor**. This system will only trigger an alert when a 'person' is detected by the AI camera **AND** the vehicle is moving above a certain speed, read from the VESC. This prevents false alarms when the vehicle is stationary."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### What Success Looks Like:\n",
    "- When a person is in view but the wheels are not spinning, there should be **NO** alert.\n",
    "- When the wheels are spinning fast but no person is in view, there should be **NO** alert.\n",
    "- When a person is in view **AND** the wheels are spinning fast, the buzzer **SHOULD** sound an alert."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 2: Combining Data\n",
    "\n",
    "To achieve our goal, we must initialize and read from both the `VESCStudentAPI` and the `AIStudentAPI` in the same script."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 2.1 - Full System Initialization\n",
    "import sys, os, time\n",
    "from gpiozero import Buzzer\n",
    "sys.path.append(os.path.abspath('../../'))\n",
    "from student_api import VESCStudentAPI, AIStudentAPI\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize Buzzer\n",
    "buzzer = Buzzer(17)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize AI System\n",
    "ai_api = AIStudentAPI()\n",
    "ai_api.start_camera()\n",
    "print(\"✅ AI Camera is live.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize VESC System\n",
    "vesc_api = VESCStudentAPI()\n",
    "vesc = None\n",
    "if vesc_api.start():\n",
    "    time.sleep(6)\n",
    "    controllers = vesc_api.get_connected_controllers()\n",
    "    if controllers:\n",
    "        vesc = vesc_api.get_controller(controllers[0])\n",
    "        print(f'✅ Connected to VESC: {vesc.controller_id}')\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print('❌ VESC: No controllers found')\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print('❌ VESC: Failed to start API')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### EXERCISE: Combined Data Loop\n",
    "In the cell below, create a `while` loop that, in each iteration, reads the **RPM** from the VESC and gets the **detections** from the AI camera. Print both values on the same line. Run it for 10 seconds. (Don't worry about displaying the video frame)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "start_time = time.time()\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    while time.time() - start_time < 10:\n",
    "        # Your code to get rpm and detections here\n",
    "        \n",
    "        rpm = None\n",
    "        detections = []\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if vesc:\n",
    "            rpm = vesc.get_rpm()\n",
    "        \n",
    "        _, detections = ai_api.get_frame_and_detections()\n",
    "            \n",
    "        # Your print statement here\n",
    "        print(f'RPM: {rpm if rpm is not None else "N/A"}, Detections: {len(detections)}')\n",
    "        \n",
    "        time.sleep(0.2)\n",
    "        clear_output(wait=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "except KeyboardInterrupt:\n",
    "    print(\"Loop stopped.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 3: Conditional Safety Logic\n",
    "\n",
    "Now we add the core of our smart system: the multi-condition `if` statement."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 3.1 - The Core Logic\n",
    "SPEED_THRESHOLD = 500 # RPM\n",
    "CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = 0.75\n",
    "TARGET_LABEL = 'person'\n",
    "\n",
    "last_alert_time = 0\n",
    "COOLDOWN = 5 # seconds\n",
    "\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    print(\"Smart Safety Monitor ACTIVE. Press Interrupt (■) to stop.\")\n",
    "    while True:\n",
    "        # 1. Get data from both sensors\n",
    "        rpm = vesc.get_rpm() if vesc else 0\n",
    "        _, detections = ai_api.get_frame_and_detections()\n",
    "        \n",
    "        is_person_detected = False\n",
    "        for det in detections:\n",
    "            if det['label'] == TARGET_LABEL and det['confidence'] > CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD:\n",
    "                is_person_detected = True\n",
    "                break\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # 2. Apply the conditional logic\n",
    "        if is_person_detected and rpm > SPEED_THRESHOLD:\n",
    "            # 3. Check cooldown and trigger alert\n",
    "            if time.time() - last_alert_time > COOLDOWN:\n",
    "                print(f\"ALERT! Person detected while moving at {rpm} RPM!\")\n",
    "                buzzer.beep(0.1, 0.1, 3)\n",
    "                last_alert_time = time.time()\n",
    "        \n",
    "        time.sleep(0.1)\n",
    "\n",
    "except KeyboardInterrupt:\n",
    "    print(\"\\nMonitor stopped.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
